cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper discusses the implementation of metaheuristic algorithms for optimizing convolution neural networks (CNN) in deep learning, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed methods on image classification datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper aims to improve the accuracy of CNN, which is a common goal in the field of artificial intelligence, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the proposed methods involve optimization and search techniques, which could also place the paper under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
